article.headline: Towson 81, James Madison 78
article.story: TOWSON, Md. -- Jarrel Smith scored 21 points and Towson defeated James Madison 81-78 on Monday night. The Tigers (6-17, 3-10 Colonial Athletic Association) led 59-44 on Isaiah Philmore's free throws with 10:51 to go. The Dukes (10-14, 3-10) pulled within 72-68 with 2:18 remaining, and sent the Tigers to the foul line the rest of the way. Towson made just 5 of 10 free throws in the final 55 seconds, allowing James Madison to chip away. The Dukes turned three instances where the Tigers made just one of two free throws into nine points. After Darren White's 3-pointer pulled James Madison within 79-78 with 5 seconds left, Troy Franklin became the only Towson player in four tries to make both his free throws, sealing the win. Rashawn Polk finished with 13 points and Robert Nwankwo added 11 for the Tigers. Denzel Bowles led the Dukes with 29 point and 13 rebounds.
